# Snakemake rules and CLI

This document provides an overview of the Snakemake workflow rules and how to interact with them using the Snakemake command-line interface (CLI).

## Snakemake CLI Overview

Snakemake provides a powerful command-line interface for executing workflows. Here are the most commonly used commands:

### Workflow conda environment initialization

After cloning the repository, first "localize" the conda environment yaml files to load the projects python package.

```bash
snakemake conda_localize
```

### Basic Execution

This will run the targets defined in the `all` rule using the profile settings in `workflow/profiles/default/config.yaml` which loads the workflow configuration from `config/`

```bash
# Run the workflow with default settings
snakemake
```

For a complete list of options, run `snakemake --help` or consult the [Snakemake documentation](https://snakemake.readthedocs.io/).

## Utility rules

### `build` rules

- `pyproject2conda` rules create environment YAML files from `pyproject.toml`.

??? info `build.smk`

