### `dev` rules

- `conda_localize` rules modify the environment YAML files so that they also install the project's python package using a full path.

- `conda_update` rule create local named conda environments for development purposes. Running `snakemake conda_update` builds all the conda environments. To only build a desired conda environment, tell snakemake to target an environment file, but replace `.yaml` with `.snakemake_conda_update_stamp`

  To create just the `{{ package_name }}-py312-dev-runner` conda environment from the localized environment file `workflow/envs/localized/{{ package_name }}-py312-dev-runner.yaml`, run:

  ```bash
  snakemake `workflow/envs/localized/{{ package_name }}-py312-dev-runner.snakemake_conda_update_stamp`
  ```

??? info `dev.smk`

    ```python
